        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 3:18PM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 317 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gillis, or near Moss Bluff, moving northwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to vegetation and outdoor
objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Charles, Sulphur, Westlake, Reeves, Dry Creek, Singer, Moss
Bluff, De Quincy, Ragley, Longville, Bivens, Buhler, Gillis, Tulla,
Oretta, and Bundick Lake.

This includes Interstate 10 in Louisiana between mile markers 28 and
31.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
